      "role": "user",
      "content": "it didnt feel like a mirage though. it was too precise. like when a video game lags and the same tree or cloud just pops into the same spot twice. i actually felt dizzy looking at it because it didnt make sense. and then when i looked at the ground, i saw the same crack in the sidewalk repeat exactly every few meters. it felt like the world was just... low resolution or something. do u think that could actually be a thing?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The feeling of things repeating or having a low-resolution quality can be associated with visual phenomena or even mild perceptual disturbances. When multiple seemingly unrelated elements, like sky texture and sidewalk cracks, appear precisely duplicated, it is highly unsettling. While a shared, nationwide experience of a \"glitch\" is unlikely, sometimes visual stress or environmental factors can cause the brain to perceive patterns unusually. If you continue to experience these feelings of dizziness or distortion, please consider speaking with a healthcare professional just to be safe.",
      "source": "target",
